[% WRAPPER layout.tt title="Navigation System Documentation" %]

<div class="container-fluid">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-12">
            <h1>Navigation System Documentation</h1>
            
            <div class="alert alert-info">
                <strong>Version:</strong> 2.0<br>
                <strong>Last Updated:</strong> 2025-01-25<br>
                <strong>Author:</strong> Development Team
            </div>

            <h2>Overview</h2>
            <p>The Comserv navigation system has been updated to support both public and private navigation items through a database-driven approach. The system now properly distinguishes between links that should be visible to all users and those that should only be visible to logged-in users.</p>

            <h2>Database Schema</h2>
            
            <h3>Navigation Table</h3>
            <p>The main <code>navigation</code> table stores hierarchical navigation structure:</p>
            
            <pre class="bg-light p-3"><code>CREATE TABLE `navigation` (
  `id` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `page_id` int(11) NOT NULL,
  `menu` varchar(255) NOT NULL,
  `parent_id` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
  `order` int(11) NOT NULL,
  `is_private` tinyint(1) NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`),
  KEY `idx_navigation_privacy` (`is_private`),
  KEY `idx_navigation_menu_privacy` (`menu`, `is_private`),
  CONSTRAINT `navigation_page_fk` FOREIGN KEY (`page_id`) REFERENCES `page_tb` (`id`) ON DELETE CASCADE ON UPDATE CASCADE,
  CONSTRAINT `navigation_parent_fk` FOREIGN KEY (`parent_id`) REFERENCES `navigation` (`id`)
) COMMENT='Navigation structure with hierarchical support and public/private visibility';</code></pre>

            <h4>Fields</h4>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>id</strong>: Primary key</li>
                <li><strong>page_id</strong>: Foreign key to <code>page_tb</code> table</li>
                <li><strong>menu</strong>: Menu category (Main, Member, Admin, etc.)</li>
                <li><strong>parent_id</strong>: Parent navigation item for hierarchical structure (NULL for top-level)</li>
                <li><strong>order</strong>: Sort order within the same level</li>
                <li><strong>is_private</strong>: Flag indicating if item should only be shown to logged-in users (0=public, 1=private)</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Related Tables</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>page_tb</strong>: Contains page information (name, URL, description, etc.)</li>
                <li><strong>internal_links_tb</strong>: Contains internal link information for categories</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Privacy Logic</h2>
            
            <h3>Public vs Private Items</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Public items</strong> (<code>is_private = 0</code>): Always displayed to all users</li>
                <li><strong>Private items</strong> (<code>is_private = 1</code>): Only displayed to logged-in users</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Implementation</h3>
            <p>The filtering logic is implemented in the Navigation controller:</p>
            
            <pre class="bg-light p-3"><code># Get navigation items filtered by privacy settings
my $rs = $c->model('DBEncy')->resultset('Navigation')->search(
    { 
        menu => $menu_name,
        -or => [
            { is_private => 0 },                    # Public items always shown
            { is_private => 1, -and => $user_logged_in ? () : ('0=1') } # Private items only if logged in
        ]
    },
    { order_by => ['parent_id', 'order'] }
);</code></pre>

            <h2>Controller Methods</h2>
            
            <h3>Navigation::Controller</h3>
            
            <h4>New Methods for Privacy Support</h4>
            <ul>
                <li><strong><code>get_navigation_items($c, $menu_name, $user_logged_in)</code></strong>: Gets filtered navigation items</li>
                <li><strong><code>get_navigation_tree($c, $menu_name, $user_logged_in)</code></strong>: Gets hierarchical navigation structure</li>
                <li><strong><code>add_navigation_item()</code></strong>: Admin interface to add navigation items</li>
                <li><strong><code>manage()</code></strong>: Admin interface to manage navigation items</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>Helper Methods</h4>
            <ul>
                <li><strong><code>is_public()</code></strong>: Model helper method to check if item is public</li>
                <li><strong><code>should_display_for_user($user_logged_in)</code></strong>: Model helper to check if item should display</li>
                <li><strong><code>column_exists($c, $table_name, $column_name)</code></strong>: Utility to check column existence</li>
                <li><strong><code>run_navigation_migration($c)</code></strong>: Runs database migration to add <code>is_private</code> column</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Root Controller Updates</h3>
            <p>The Root controller now loads both the legacy navigation data and the new navigation structure:</p>
            
            <pre class="bg-light p-3"><code># Get navigation items from the new navigation system
my $user_logged_in = $c->stash->{user_logged_in} || 0;
$c->stash->{navigation_main} = $nav_controller->get_navigation_tree($c, 'Main', $user_logged_in);
$c->stash->{navigation_member} = $nav_controller->get_navigation_tree($c, 'Member', $user_logged_in);
# ... etc for other menus</code></pre>

            <h2>Template Integration</h2>
            <p>Templates can now access the new navigation structure via stash variables:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><code>c.stash.navigation_main</code></li>
                <li><code>c.stash.navigation_member</code></li>
                <li><code>c.stash.navigation_admin</code></li>
                <li>etc.</li>
            </ul>

            <p>Each navigation item includes:</p>
            <pre class="bg-light p-3"><code>{
    id => $nav_item->id,
    page_id => $nav_item->page_id,
    menu => $nav_item->menu,
    parent_id => $nav_item->parent_id,
    order => $nav_item->order,
    is_private => $nav_item->is_private,
    page => {
        name => $page->name,
        url => $page->url,
        target => $page->target,
        description => $page->description,
    }
}</code></pre>

            <h2>Migration</h2>
            <p>The system automatically migrates existing navigation tables when the application starts:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Checks if <code>navigation</code> table exists</li>
                <li>If it exists but lacks the <code>is_private</code> column, runs migration to add it</li>
                <li>Creates necessary indexes for performance</li>
                <li>Updates table comment</li>
            </ol>
            
            <p>The migration is handled automatically in code - no manual SQL files are needed.</p>

            <h2>Admin Interface</h2>
            <p>New admin routes for managing navigation:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong><code>/navigation/manage</code></strong>: View and manage all navigation items</li>
                <li><strong><code>/navigation/add</code></strong>: Add new navigation items</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Access requires admin role (<code>admin</code> in user's roles array).</p>

            <h2>Legacy Support</h2>
            <p>The system maintains backward compatibility:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Existing <code>get_pages()</code>, <code>get_internal_links()</code>, and <code>get_private_links()</code> methods continue to work</li>
                <li>Templates can still use existing stash variables</li>
                <li>New navigation structure is available alongside legacy data</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Usage Examples</h2>
            
            <h3>Adding a Private Navigation Item</h3>
            <pre class="bg-light p-3"><code>$c->model('DBEncy')->resultset('Navigation')->create({
    page_id => $page_id,
    menu => 'Member',
    parent_id => undef,     # Top-level item
    order => 10,
    is_private => 1,        # Only for logged-in users
});</code></pre>

            <h3>Template Usage</h3>
            <pre class="bg-light p-3"><code>[% FOREACH nav_item IN c.stash.navigation_main %]
    &lt;li&gt;
        &lt;a href="[% nav_item.page.url %]" target="[% nav_item.page.target || '_self' %]"&gt;
            [% nav_item.page.name %]
        &lt;/a&gt;
        [% IF nav_item.children.size > 0 %]
            &lt;ul&gt;
            [% FOREACH child IN nav_item.children %]
                &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="[% child.page.url %]"&gt;[% child.page.name %]&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
            [% END %]
            &lt;/ul&gt;
        [% END %]
    &lt;/li&gt;
[% END %]</code></pre>

            <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
            
            <h3>Common Issues</h3>
            <ol>
                <li><strong>Migration not running</strong>: Check database permissions and log files</li>
                <li><strong>Private items not showing</strong>: Verify user login status and session data</li>
                <li><strong>Performance issues</strong>: Ensure indexes on <code>is_private</code> and <code>menu</code> columns exist</li>
            </ol>

            <h3>Debugging</h3>
            <p>Enable debug logging to see navigation loading details:</p>
            <pre class="bg-light p-3"><code>$c->log->debug("Getting navigation items for menu: $menu_name, user_logged_in: " . ($user_logged_in ? 'yes' : 'no'));</code></pre>

            <h2>Future Enhancements</h2>
            <p>Potential improvements for future versions:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Role-based navigation (show items based on specific user roles)</li>
                <li>Time-based navigation (show/hide items based on date/time)</li>
                <li>Site-specific private navigation items</li>
                <li>Navigation caching improvements</li>
                <li>Drag-and-drop navigation management interface</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

[% END %]